    <h1>Short Film Clinic</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline">WHEN: INFO: WHEN: INFO: This art prize aims to sup&#xAD;port the pro&#xAD;fes&#xAD;sional de&#xAD;vel&#xAD;op&#xAD;ment of emerg&#xAD;ing tal&#xAD;ent in Sin&#xAD;ga&#xAD;pore&#x2019;s vis&#xAD;ual WHEN: AD&#xAD;MIS&#xAD;SION: INFO: WHEN: AD&#xAD;MIS&#xAD;SION: INFO: WHEN: INFO:</span>
    </section>

    <p>Sub­mit by Aug 30 bit.ly/33N4ra2</p>
    <p>The clinic by the Sin­ga­pore Film Com­mis­sion is open to di­rec­tors and/or pro­duc­ers with com­pleted short films or in-de­vel­op­ment scripts. They are en­cour­aged to regis­ter as a direc­tor and/or pro­ducer team. Se­lected par­tic­i­pants will at­tend one-on-one con­sul­ta­tions with in­ter­na­tional men­tors on fes­ti­val and dig­i­tal dis­tri­bu­tion strate­gies for their short films.</p>
    <p>Regis­ter by Sun; clinic is on Sept 10 & 11 bit.ly/3kBUcLF</p>
    <p>Im­part Awards 2021</p>
    <p>arts scene by pro­vid­ing im­pact­ful ca­reer-build­ing op­por­tu­ni­ties. In this edi­tion, three win­ners will be se­lected in the artist or cu­ra­tor cat­e­gory. Each win­ner will re­ceive a cash award and an in­ter­na­tional ex­change with vis­its to renowned art in­sti­tu­tions.</p>
    <p>Till Oct 16</p>
    <p>Free bit.ly/3ahxJid</p>
    <p>Sin­ga­pore Sym­phony Chil­dren’s Choir Au­di­tions</p>
    <p>The choir of­fers train­ing and per­for­mance op­por­tu­ni­ties to chil­dren – such as de­vel­op­ing their vo­cal tech­nique, mu­sic lit­er­acy and mu­si­cian­ship – with an aim to help fledg­ling singers achieve their mu­si­cal po­ten­tial. Be­sides its own con­certs, the choir also of­fers the ex­pe­ri­ence of per­form­ing cho­ral clas­sics with the com­bined forces of the Sin­ga­pore Sym­phony Cho­rus and Orches­tra. Open to chil­dren aged eight (born in 2012) to 14. Ap­pli­cants aged 11 and above must have a min­i­mum of ABRSM Mu­sic The­ory Grade 3. The au­di­tions will be con­ducted on­line.</p>
    <p>Regis­ter by Sept 13</p>
    <p>$25 a par­tic­i­pant bit.ly/2PKmCF3</p>
    <p>Ex­ten­sion Of Open Call: Ma­hogany Jour­nal</p>
    <p>Ma­hogany Jour­nal, an on­line plat­form for South Asian writ­ers and read­ers in Sin­ga­pore, is look­ing for more short sto­ries to be pub­lished in its sec­ond is­sue, ti­tled Retellings. Un­pub­lished fic­tional tales about myths, le­gends and folk­lore, as well as new po­etry works, are wel­come. Writ­ers must be of South Asian back­ground and be from or based in Sin­ga­pore. They will be paid $15 for po­ems and $30 for short sto­ries.</p>
    <p>Sub­mis­sion dead­line ex­tended to mid­night</p>
    <p>bit.ly/3ixxGSf</p>


